{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Remote sensing and geospatial analysis AI processes satellite imagery and remote sensing data to map disaster impacts and monitor environmental changes (Composto et al., 2025; Singh and Hoskere, 2023).",
    "ML algorithms analyze Sentinel-1 and Sentinel-2 imagery to enhance flood extent mapping, leveraging the Normalized Difference Water Index (NDWI) and Google Earth Engine (GEE) for near-real-time assessments (Composto et al., 2025).",
    "AI also supports wildfire and landslide vulnerability mapping by integrating topographic and vegetation data (Fernández-Guisuraga et al., 2024; Kerle et al., 2019).",
    "AI-driven DSS integrate predictive models, risk assessments, and real-time data streams to support decision-making in disaster response (Cilli et al., 2022; Hahn et al., 2024).",
    "Early Warning Systems (EWS) analyze sensor data, weather patterns, and social media activity to detect hazards and guide evacuation protocols (Hahn et al., 2024)."
  ],
